---
import Canvas from "../layouts/Canvas.astro";
const styles = `
    .boundary {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      gap: 0;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      overflow: hidden;
      background: var(--card);
    }
    .boundary-item {
      padding: 18px 20px;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .boundary-item:nth-child(3n) { border-right: 0; }
    .boundary-label {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 10.5px;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    .boundary-title { font-weight: 600; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
    .boundary-body { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.55; }
    .packet {
      display: grid;
      gap: 8px;
      counter-reset: packet;
    }
    .packet-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 42px 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      background: var(--card);
    }
    .packet-row::before {
      counter-increment: packet;
      content: counter(packet, decimal-leading-zero);
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11px;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      align-self: center;
    }
    .packet-title { font-weight: 600; font-size: 13.5px; margin-bottom: 2px; }
    .packet-desc { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5; }
    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .boundary-item { border-right: 0; }
    }
  `;
---

<Canvas title="23 · Agent Credit — Sardis Canvas" currentId="credit">
<Fragment slot="head">
  <style is:global set:html={styles}></style>
</Fragment>

<section class="hero">
  <span class="eyebrow">Canvas 23 · Product</span>
  <h1>Agent Credit — facility access without Sardis becoming the lender.</h1>
  <p class="hero-lead">
    Facility Gate is Sardis's credit control plane for agents. It lets an agent request temporary
    purchase authority against a partner-backed facility, but keeps Sardis out of custody, issuing,
    balance-sheet lending, and collections. Sardis decides whether authority exists; the sponsor or
    partner remains the economic actor.
  </p>
  <div class="row row-wrap mt-24" style="gap:12px;">
    <span class="badge badge-info">New</span>
    <span class="badge">Facility Gate</span>
    <span class="badge">Non-custodial control plane</span>
    <span class="badge">Simulator-first</span>
    <span class="badge badge-muted">No live card issuance by default</span>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="padding-top:0; border-top:0;">
  <div class="callout callout-info">
    <span class="callout-title">TL;DR</span>
    Sardis does not hand an agent a general-purpose credit card. The agent submits a facility request;
    Sardis loads persisted mandate, facility, policy, risk, evidence, revocation, and liability state;
    then appends an immutable decision packet. Execution is gated through a simulator today and a
    provider adapter later. Authorization and money movement stay separated.
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">Boundary</div>
    <h2>The product is a credit authority firewall.</h2>
    <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:760px;">
      The architecture deliberately avoids the tempting but dangerous framing: "credit card for agents."
      A card is only one possible execution rail. The durable primitive is delegated facility authority.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="grid grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">What Sardis controls</div>
      <div class="card-description">
        Identity binding, mandate scope, policy evaluation, risk scoring, evidence capture, human step-up,
        authorization, revocation, exception handling, and audit reconstruction. These are control-plane
        functions, not custody functions.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">What Sardis does not become</div>
      <div class="card-description">
        Sardis is not the lender, issuer of record, stored-value holder, collections system, or repayment
        obligor. Liquidity and settlement belong to the sponsor, customer-controlled account, or partner
        facility provider.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">Control plane</div>
    <h2>How a facility request actually moves.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="diagram">
    <pre class="mermaid" is:raw>
flowchart TB
    A["Agent<br/>request"] --> FG["Sardis Facility Gate"]
    FG --> M["Persisted mandate<br/>+ facility versions"]
    FG --> P["Policy, risk,<br/>evidence, revocation"]
    P --> D{"Decision"}

    D -->|"approved"| L1["Append approved<br/>decision packet"]
    L1 --> X["Execution adapter"]
    X --> S["Simulator now"]
    X --> R["Partner rail later"]

    D -->|"step-up"| L2["Append step-up<br/>decision"]
    L2 --> O["Approval queue"]
    O --> P2["Recheck revocation<br/>+ facility state"]
    P2 --> L3["Append final<br/>decision"]

    D -->|"denied"| L4["Append denial<br/>with reason codes"]
    L1 --> AU["Audit link"]
    L3 --> AU
    L4 --> AU
    AU --> A
    </pre>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">Non-custodial line</div>
    <h2>Where custody stays out of Sardis.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="boundary">
    <div class="boundary-item">
      <div class="boundary-label">Agent</div>
      <div class="boundary-title">Delegated actor</div>
      <div class="boundary-body">Can request authority and attach evidence. Cannot create a facility, expand a limit, or become the repayment obligor.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="boundary-item">
      <div class="boundary-label">Sponsor</div>
      <div class="boundary-title">Economic principal</div>
      <div class="boundary-body">Owns the mandate and liability. The audit packet names the repayment obligor and loss owner explicitly.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="boundary-item">
      <div class="boundary-label">Sardis</div>
      <div class="boundary-title">Authority control plane</div>
      <div class="boundary-body">Evaluates, gates, records, revokes, and reconstructs decisions. It does not hold funds or issue credit.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="boundary-item">
      <div class="boundary-label">Facility</div>
      <div class="boundary-title">Partner-backed liquidity</div>
      <div class="boundary-body">Represents an external or sponsor-backed line. Sardis stores state and version refs, not the balance-sheet obligation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="boundary-item">
      <div class="boundary-label">Adapter</div>
      <div class="boundary-title">Execution gate</div>
      <div class="boundary-body">Simulator today; real provider later. No credential is created unless an authorization event already exists.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="boundary-item">
      <div class="boundary-label">Partner</div>
      <div class="boundary-title">Rail / issuing / settlement</div>
      <div class="boundary-body">Moves money or provides credit under its own contract. Webhooks mirror external state back into append-only events.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">Decision packet</div>
    <h2>Every approval is reconstructable.</h2>
    <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:760px;">
      The audit surface is not a screenshot of current state. It is a versioned packet that says exactly
      what Sardis knew and which authority it relied on when the decision happened.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="packet">
    <div class="packet-row">
      <div>
        <div class="packet-title">Mandate version</div>
        <div class="packet-desc">Explicit facility draw authority, agent binding, merchant/category scope, draw caps, approval threshold.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="packet-row">
      <div>
        <div class="packet-title">Facility version</div>
        <div class="packet-desc">Provider, sponsor, status, limit payload, allowed categories, blocked merchants, repayment mirror if present.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="packet-row">
      <div>
        <div class="packet-title">Policy and risk versions</div>
        <div class="packet-desc">Deterministic policy snapshot, risk model version, feature snapshot, reason codes. No hidden model magic.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="packet-row">
      <div>
        <div class="packet-title">Evidence considered</div>
        <div class="packet-desc">Only evidence attached before decision time is considered. Later evidence requires a new decision path.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="packet-row">
      <div>
        <div class="packet-title">Liability assignment</div>
        <div class="packet-desc">Repayment obligor, sponsor, loss owner, and facility provider are first-class fields, not buried in metadata.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="packet-row">
      <div>
        <div class="packet-title">Event hash chain</div>
        <div class="packet-desc">Requests, approvals, executions, exceptions, revocations, webhooks, and exports sit on append-only events.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">Pilot shape</div>
    <h2>What is live in the repo now.</h2>
  </div>
  <table class="data">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Surface</th><th>Status</th><th>Why it matters</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Feature gate</td><td><span class="badge badge-success">pilot-ready</span></td><td>Global enablement plus <code>SARDIS_FACILITY_GATE_ORG_ALLOWLIST</code> prevents broad accidental exposure.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Strict authority</td><td><span class="badge badge-success">pilot-ready</span></td><td>Authorization loads persisted mandate, facility, and policy records instead of trusting request snapshots.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Simulator adapter</td><td><span class="badge badge-success">default</span></td><td>Exercises execution semantics without live provider money movement.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Real provider</td><td><span class="badge badge-muted">disabled</span></td><td>Provider adapter work stays behind contract tests, sandbox credentials, and capability acceptance.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Pilot readiness</td><td><span class="badge badge-success">scripted</span></td><td><code>facility_gate_pilot_readiness.py</code> checks flags, allowlist, alert artifacts, and tabletop evidence.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Live card issuance</td><td><span class="badge badge-warning">not yet</span></td><td>Intentionally out of scope until revocation, audit, adapter, webhook, and partner semantics are accepted.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="eyebrow">Related canvases</div>
    <h2>Read next.</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="grid grid-2">
    <a class="canvas-card" href="/policy-engine">
      <div class="canvas-card-num">08 · Flows</div>
      <div class="canvas-card-title">Policy Engine</div>
      <div class="canvas-card-desc">The deterministic enforcement layer Facility Gate composes with.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="canvas-card" href="/dual-rail">
      <div class="canvas-card-num">22 · Protocol</div>
      <div class="canvas-card-title">Dual-Rail Architecture</div>
      <div class="canvas-card-desc">Where facility-backed authority fits into the broader rail strategy.</div>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>
</Canvas>
